'''Pit racing''' was a popular&mdash;yet illegal&mdash;sport practiced in the [[garbage pit]]s of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. Contestants competed in unique, individually-made [[Racing wings|pit racers]], gliders in which they descended the garbage pits to the lowest levels, where they collected scales from the backs of [[garbage worm]]s. The sport was highly dangerous and subject to [[Judicial/Legends|Judicial]] raids, since garbage canisters, regularly ejected from the pits into [[Orbit/Legends|orbit]], could kill the competitors. Pit racing had been practiced since approximately [[129 BBY]].<ref name="Rogue Planet">''[[Rogue Planet]]'' mentions that the sport was invented "perhaps a century before" [[29 BBY/Legends|29 BBY]].</ref> Successful pit racers included [[Reymet Autem]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]], who frequented the [[Wicko District]] garbage pits. [[Jahan Cross]] was also familiar with the sport, having done it in his youth.<ref name="Agent of the Empire – Iron Eclipse 1">[[Agent of the Empire – Iron Eclipse 1|''Agent of the Empire – Iron Eclipse'' 1]]</ref>

